Austrian Josef Koeberl stands in a glass cabin filled with ice during his world record attempt in Vienna on Saturday. With a time of two hours, eight minutes and 47 seconds, Koeberl beat the previous world record time spent in direct, full-body contact with ice of one hour, 53 minutes and 10 seconds achieved by Chinese athlete Jin Songhao in 2014. Photo: IC  
